05/barbarian-invasions-and-statement-take-home-national-board-review-honours |title=News Releases |date=5 December 2003 |accessdate=27 August 2016|publisher=[[Telefilm Canada]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924050747/https://www.telefilm.ca/en/news/releases/2003/12/05/barbarian-invasions-and-statement-take-home-national-board-review-honours |archivedate=24 September 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| Top Foreign Films\n| {{won}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Toronto Film Critics Association]]\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Toronto Film Critics Association Awards 2003|17 December 2003]]\n| [[Toronto Film Critics Association Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]] \n| rowspan=\"2\" | Denys Arcand\n| {{won}}{{efn|Shared with [[Sofia Coppola]] for ''[[Lost in Translation (film)|Lost in Translation]]''}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" | <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://torontofilmcritics.com/past-award-winners/|title=Past Award Winners|accessdate=27 August 2016|publisher=[[Toronto Film Critics Association]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150715181549/http://torontofilmcritics.com/past-award-winners/|archive-date=15 July 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[Toronto International Film Festival]]\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[2003 Toronto International Film Festival|4\u201313 September 2003]]\n| [[Toronto International Film Festival Award for Best Canadian Film|Best Canadian Feature Film]] \n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" | <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/barbarian-invasions-is-canadas-entry-for-oscar/article1166357/ |title=Barbarian Invasions is Canada's entry for Oscar |last=[[Canadian Press]] |date=18 September 2003 |accessdate=27 August 2016 |work=[[The Globe and Mail]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918102454/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/barbarian-invasions-is-canadas-entry-for-oscar/article1166357/ |archive-date=18 September 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" rowspan=5| [[Vancouver Film Critics Circle]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" | [[Vancouver Film Critics Circle Awards 2003|2 February 2004]]\n| [[Vancouver Film Critics Circle Award for Best Canadian Film|Best Canadian Feature Film]] \n| ''The Barbarian Invasions''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" | <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://vancouverfilmcritics.com/2004/02/02/4th-annual-award-winners/ |title=4th Annual Award Winners |date=2 February 2004 |accessdate=28 August 2016 |publisher=[[Vancouver Film Critics Circle]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160913060757/https://vancouverfilmcritics.com/2004/02/02/4th-annual-award-winners/ |archive-date=13 September 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Vancouver Film Critics Circle Award for Best Director of a Canadian Film|Best Canadian Director]]\n| Denys Arcand\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Vancouver Film Critics Circle Award for Best Actor in a Canadian Film|Best Actor in a Canadian Film]]\n| R\u00e9my Girard\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Vancouver Film Critics Circle Award for Best Actress in a Canadian Film|Best Actress in a Canadian Film]]\n| Marie-Jos\u00e9e Croze\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Vancouver Film Critics Circle Award for Best Supporting Actor in a Canadian Film|Best Supporting Actor in a Canadian Film]]\n| St\u00e9phane Rousseau\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Legacy==\nIn 2007, Arcand's film ''[[Days of Darkness (2007 Canadian film)|Days of Darkness]]'' was released. While considered part of a loose trilogy following ''[[The Decline of the American Empire]]'' and ''The Barbarian Invasions'',<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2008/03/21/days_of_darkness_arcand_triumph.html |title='Days of Darkness': Arcand triumph |last=Howell |first=Peter |date=21 March 2008 |accessdate=30 December 2016 |work=[[The Toronto Star]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202003347/https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2008/03/21/days_of_darkness_arcand_triumph.html |archive-date=2 February 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"HaysCBC\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.cbc.ca/arts/tiff/features/tiffarcand.html |title=Dark shadows |last=Hays |first=Matthew |date=14 September 2007 |accessdate=30 December 2016 |work=[[CBC News]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161231171635/http://www.cbc.ca/arts/tiff/features/tiffarcand.html |archive-date=31 December 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Coulombe\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.lactualite.com/culture/quest-ce-qui-cloche-avec-denys-arcand/ |title=Qu\u2019est-ce qui cloche avec Denys Arcand ? |last=Coulombe |first=Michel |date=8 November 2007 |accessdate=30 December 2016 |work=[[L'actualit\u00e9]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161231061947/http://www.lactualite.com/culture/quest-ce-qui-cloche-avec-denys-arcand/ |archive-date=31 December 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Arcand acknowledged in a 2007 interview ''Days of Darkness'' had more similarities to his less successful 2000 film ''[[Stardom]]''.<ref name=\"Coulombe\"/> [[Johanne-Marie Tremblay]] reprised her role as Constance from ''Jesus of Montreal'' and ''The Barbarian Invasions''.{{sfn|Pike|2012|p=105}} In 2018, Arcand's ''[[The Fall of the American Empire]]'' followed similar themes.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://voir.ca/nouvelles/actualite-cinematographique/2018/03/08/denys-arcand-devoile-une-premiere-bande-annonce-de-la-chute-de-lempire-americain/ |title=Denys Arcand D\u00e9voile Une Premi\u00e8re Bande-Annonce De La Chute De L'empire Am\u00e9ricain |last=Lods |first=Jeanne |date=25 July 2017 |accessdate=9 April 2018 |work=[[Voir]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180410134910/https://voir.ca/nouvelles/actualite-cinematographique/2018/03/08/denys-arcand-devoile-une-premiere-bande-annonce-de-la-chute-de-lempire-americain/ |archive-date=10 April 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 76th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of Canadian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n* {{cite book |last=Boyd|first=Susan C. |title=Hooked: Drug War Films in Britain, Canada, and the U.S. |publisher=Routledge|date=2008 |isbn=0203930738 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite magazine |last=Howell|first=Peter |date=September\u2013December 2003 |title=A Director in His Prime: Denys Arcand's Les Invasions barbares|magazine=[[Take One (Canadian magazine)|Take One]] |location= |publisher= |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Loiselle|first=Andr\u00e9 |title=Denys Arcand's Le D\u00e9clin de L'empire Am\u00e9ricain and Les Invasions Barbares |location=Toronto, Buffalo and London |publisher=University of Toronto Press |date=2008 |isbn=0802099335 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Melnyk|first=George |title=Great Canadian Film Directors |url=https://archive.org/details/greatcanadianfil00meln|url-access=registration|publisher=The University of Alberta Press|date=2007|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Pike|first=David Lawrence |title=Canadian Cinema Since the 1980s: At the Heart of the World |location=Toronto, Buffalo and London |publisher=University of Toronto Press|date=2012 |isbn=1442698322 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Thompson|first=Wayne C. |title=Canada 2014 |publisher=Rowman and Littlefield|date=2014 |edition=30 |isbn=147581240X |ref=harv}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.miramax.com/movie/barbarian-invasions}}\n* {{IMDb title|0338135}}\n* {{Allmovie title|285687}}\n* {{mojo title|barbarianinvasions}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|barbarian_invasions}}\n* {{metacritic film|the-barbarian-invasions}}\n\n{{Denys Arcand}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for ''The Barbarian Invasions''\n|list =\n{{AcademyAwardBestForeignLanguageFilm 2001\u20132020}}\n{{ACCT Best Picture}}\n{{C\u00e9sar Award for Best Film}}\n{{Broadcast Film Critics Association Award for Best Foreign Language Film}}\n{{Lumi\u00e8res Award for Best French-Language Film}}\n{{National Board of Review