 J. |date=4 May 2012 |accessdate=27 August 2016 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120513214849/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/caesar-die-tops-donatello-award-320415 |archive-date=13 May 2012 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[European Film Awards]]\n| [[16th European Film Awards|6 December 2003]]\n| [[European Film Award for Best Non-European Film|Best Non-European Film]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" | <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://playbackonline.ca/2004/01/05/globe-20040105/ |title=Invasions gets Golden nom |last=Playback Staff |date=5 January 2004 |accessdate=28 August 2016 |work=[[Playback (magazine)|Playback]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911015650/http://playbackonline.ca/2004/01/05/globe-20040105/ |archive-date=11 September 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" rowspan=9| [[Genie Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"9\" | [[24th Genie Awards|1 May 2004]]\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Motion Picture|Best Motion Picture]]\n| Denise Robert, Daniel Louis and [[Fabienne Vonier]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"9\" | <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://oldads.playbackmag.com/articles/magazine/20040329/genlist.html?print=yes |title=Genie countdown: Who will get the nod? |last=Staff |date=29 March 2004 |accessdate=19 April 2017 |work=[[Playback (magazine)|Playback]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170419220148/http://oldads.playbackmag.com/articles/magazine/20040329/genlist.html?print=yes |archive-date=19 April 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/barbarian-invasions-is-gem-of-genies/article1136905/ |title=Barbarian Invasions is gem of Genies |last=[[The Canadian Press]] |first= |date=2 May 2004 |accessdate=21 April 2017 |work=[[The Globe and Mail]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Achievement in Direction|Best Direction]]\n| Denys Arcand\n| 